The article highlights President Biden's address on the 100th day of his administration. He reflects on inheriting a nation in crisis, including the pandemic, economic crisis, and attack on democracy. However, he states that America is now on the move again, turning crisis into opportunity and setback into strength. He addresses concerns of people feeling left behind in a changing economy and emphasizes that the American Jobs Plan will create millions of good-paying jobs that cannot be outsourced. He also emphasizes the importance of the middle class and unions in building the country. Additionally, he mentions the need to restore faith in democracy and highlights the administration's achievements in vaccinating the nation, creating jobs, and delivering results that benefit the people.